Ive been playing around with my two networked PC's recently and trying different operating systems. Here's my opinion on those i know of.<br>
<br>
Win ME... not too bad it seems to like EQ, i get the occasional lock up but its pretty rare. Im running 768 RAM on my main PC and there seem to be no issues concerning having over 512 ram.<br>
<br>
Win98SE... Got this installed on my slave PC and its more stable than ME. I think this is as close to getting a gold star as microsoft have been for a few years.<br>
<br>
Win XP.. forget it.. oh it looks great and its built around the NT file system but it has so many bugs in it that it only lasted about a week on my PC before being junked.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
My advice(for what its worth) stick with 98SE.. and look elsewhere for the causes of any problems you are having.. it could be a corrupt windows installation but it could also be any number of other problems and installing XP certainly didnt fix anything for me<br>
